article.headline: Rutgers 67, Lehigh 61
article.story: PISCATAWAY, N.J. (AP) -- After going scoreless in his last game, Marquis Webb scored 14 points Friday night to lead Rutgers to a 67-61 win over Lehigh. Adrian Hill had his first career double-double with 10 points and 10 rebounds as the Scarlet Knights (6-5) won their fifth straight game. Lehigh's Jose Olivero led all scorers with 22 points, and Bryan White added 17 for the Mountain Hawks (5-9). After taking a 31-27 lead to halftime, the Scarlet Knights came out flat in the second half as Lehigh went on a 21-8 run. White sparked the run with two dunks and two blocks. But Rutgers answered with a 19-3 run started by an Ollie Bailey three-point play with 7:47 remaining. The Knights hit three shots from beyond the arc in the final seven minutes to help them pull away. Courtney Nelson's 3-pointer with 1:15 remaining put the Knights up 61-51. The Mountain Hawks committed 11 turnovers in the second half.
